snippet.textDisplay:
A lot of people are suggesting using the 70k for CV, which is fair enough and definitely a situation that needs some assistance. But as my favorite meme to come out of the CV situation says: How boomers feel about CV right now is how millennials feel about climate change all the time.

Instead of using the money for a short term problem why not use it for ong term impact. Donate to an environmental cause like Oceana or any that you believe in. There are also volunteering "vacations." You could find a good one and involve a subscriber or two as well as some strangers, get together with a company that is doing good work for a week, and make a difference. Whatever money you have left, donate to them.

Another idea that requires almost no $ - You guys live right by the beach. You could organize a yesfam beach cleanup, invite some strangers to come along, and do some good. Make sure to recycle whatever you can before sending the rest to the landfill.

Whatever you decide I'm excited to see how you'll use that money to do some good in the world.
